        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 6:00PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 600 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Toccoa, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Toccoa, Boydville, and Hollywood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
